DAY 3 — CURL COMMANDS (FINAL)
1️⃣ Start the server
node index.js


Make sure you see:

PostgreSQL connected
Call Orchestration Service is running on port 3000

2️⃣ Simulate Inbound Call START
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/webhooks/inbound -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"from\":\"+919876543210\",\"event\":\"call.started\"}"

✅ Expected response
{
  "message": "Inbound call started",
  "call": {
    "direction": "inbound",
    "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
  }
}

3️⃣ Simulate Inbound Call END
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/webhooks/inbound -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"from\":\"+919876543210\",\"event\":\"call.ended\"}"

✅ Expected response
{
  "message": "Inbound call completed",
  "call": {
    "status": "COMPLETED",
    "outcome": "inbound_completed"
  }
}

4️⃣ Verify DB state (VERY IMPORTANT)
curl http://localhost:3000/api/calls

You must see:
direction: inbound
status: COMPLETED
outcome: inbound_completed